Git Commands:


Creating a git repository:


$ git init   				//hidden folder for tracking the repository

$ git status				//to check the files/changes for tracking

$ git add <file>			//to start add files for tracking

$ git config user.email "example@gmail.com"

$ git config user.name "example"

$ git commit -m ".......commit message........."

$ git add *.*                           //add everything with extensions

$ git add .				//add everything which is not added or ignored.


Adding a remote repository:

$ git remote add origin http://git..... // add link to your repository created on Github

$ git push -u origin master             // push to remote repository


Unrelated histories error when trying to pull:

$ git pull origin master --allow-unrelated-histories


Pulling:

$ git pull origin master  		// pull latest from the remote repository


Pushing:

$ git push -u origin master


Branches and Merging:

$ git branch <name>			//create branch with a name

$ git checkout <name>			// checkout branch





